//    <i> [Bits 7..6] RW (@ 0x400A3806) \nSelection of 8-bit, 16-bit, or 32-bit Counter Mode\n0 : 00 = The interval timer operates in 8-bit counter mode.\n1 : 01 = The interval timer operates in 16-bit counter mode (channels 0 to 1 are used together, and channels 2 to 3 are used together).\n2 : 10 = The interval timer operates in 32-bit counter mode (channels 0 to 3 are used together).\n3 : 11 = Setting prohibited. </i>
